Interface IPolicyPeriodDiffPlugin

    Plugin that customizes policy period diff behavior.

    • Method Detail

      • compareBranches

        java.util.List<DiffItem> compareBranches(DiffReason diffReason,
                                         PolicyPeriod p1,
                                         PolicyPeriod p2)
        Compare two policy periods, returning a list of DiffItems representing the differences between them. This method is called in 3 places:
        • Multi-quote
        • Comparing PolicyPeriods of a Policy
        • Comparing Jobs of a Policy

        An implementation of this method would walk the PolicyPeriods graphs comparing fields on related beans within the graphs. Fields don't necessarily need to be different, you could highlight the fact that two fields are the same across periods.

        To add a new item create a new instance of DiffProperty, DiffAdd, or DiffRemove. When creating a new DiffProperty use the bean from p1 as the main bean, and the bean from p2 as the "based on" bean. A DiffAdd designated that the bean exists in p1 but not in p2. A DiffRemove designates that the bean exists in p2 but not in p1. You can use utilities found on DiffUtils to help you compare beans or bean graphs.

        Parameters:
        diffReason - Reason for calling Diff code
        p1 - "source" PolicyPeriod
        p2 - PolicyPeriod to compare against
        Returns:
        A list of DiffItems that represents the differences between the PolicyPeriods

      • filterDiffItems

        java.util.List<DiffItem> filterDiffItems(DiffReason diffReason,
                                         PolicyPeriod p,
                                         java.util.List<DiffItem> items)
        Filters a list of DiffItems that originates from the database. This method is called in 4 places:
        • Displaying differences between a PolicyPeriod and its based on PolicyPeriods during a policy change
        • To determine out-of-sequence transaction conflicts on a PolicyPeriod
        • To determine preemption conflicts on a PolicyPeriod
        • To determine the changes to communicate to an integration point when a new PolicyPeriod is bound

        The input set of DiffItems is derived from the database and therefore represents a database POV of these changes. By filtering the items you can provide a more intuitive summary of the differences. See the Difference class (in Gosu) for how these DiffItems are displayed in the UI.

        Parameters:
        diffReason - Reason for calling Diff code
        p - PolicyPeriod associated with the DiffItems
        items - Original set of DiffItems @return A filtered set of DiffItems.
        Returns:
        The filtered list of DiffItems
